cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use proofbundle, please cite it as below."
title: proofbundle
abstract: >-
  Emit and verify, fully offline, portable cryptographic evidence bundles (Ed25519 + RFC 6962
  Merkle + optional SD-JWT), and eval receipts that prove a model passed a threshold without
  revealing the model or the data. A verification layer for trustworthy evaluation logs.
authors:
  - family-names: Gruszka
    given-names: Konrad
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0009-0006-8947-6065"
type: software
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/b7n0de/proofbundle"
url: "https://github.com/b7n0de/proofbundle"
version: 0.7.0
# doi: add once Zenodo archives a release and assigns a DOI (none assigned yet — see the human checklist).
keywords:
  - cryptography
  - merkle
  - transparency-log
  - ed25519
  - sd-jwt
  - eval
  - attestation
  - provenance
